WEBVTT

00:02.540 --> 00:05.000
Meredith:
If you're in an O.R.

00:05.000 --> 00:06.170
and it feels like
the sky is falling...
Hey.

00:06.170 --> 00:07.170
...that's because sometimes,

00:07.170 --> 00:09.380
unfortunately, it is.
Hey.

00:09.380 --> 00:11.120
Why don't you call in sick today
and I will, too?

00:11.120 --> 00:12.460
♪ Let the good vibes roll ♪

00:12.460 --> 00:14.670
Bailey's probably gonna
fire me soon anyways.

00:14.670 --> 00:18.250
I've missed
so much already.

00:18.250 --> 00:21.380
I could go in late,
though.

00:21.380 --> 00:23.790
I was once doing
a laparoscopic appendectomy,

00:23.790 --> 00:24.830
perfectly routine...

00:24.830 --> 00:26.500
[ Knock on door ]

00:26.500 --> 00:28.000
Maggie: Meredith! Open up!
[ Knock on door ]

00:28.000 --> 00:29.380
...when out of nowhere,

00:29.380 --> 00:31.580
my patient developed
an air embolus.

00:31.580 --> 00:33.960
[ Sighs ]
Carbon dioxide that was
filling his abdomen

00:33.960 --> 00:35.460
leached into his circulation.

00:35.460 --> 00:37.710
♪ I don't know about
you, you, you ♪

00:37.710 --> 00:39.380
-What?
-Were you gonna tell us?

00:39.380 --> 00:40.580
Tell you what?

00:40.580 --> 00:42.620
It just keeps going on.

00:42.620 --> 00:43.750
What keeps going on?

00:43.750 --> 00:44.960
Your article.

00:44.960 --> 00:46.080
You wrote your article?
No!

00:46.080 --> 00:47.960
His blood pressure plummeted

00:47.960 --> 00:51.040
as the air bubble went to
his heart, causing utter chaos.

00:51.040 --> 00:53.170
This is savage.
You went after everybody --

00:53.170 --> 00:55.290
Big Pharma, insurance,

00:55.290 --> 00:56.830
institutionalized
discrimination.

00:56.830 --> 00:58.830
Wait. I-I didn't
write an article.

00:58.830 --> 01:02.540
I-I sent them, like, some ideas
that I could write about

01:02.540 --> 01:04.750
with, like, headline
and description,

01:04.750 --> 01:06.420
and they could
choose one.

01:06.420 --> 01:09.080
I started CPR, trying to keep
blood flowing to his brain.

01:09.080 --> 01:11.330
Well, they chose.

01:11.330 --> 01:13.880
We placed a central line
as quickly as we could,

01:13.880 --> 01:16.580
but before we knew it, his
lungs were filling with fluid.

01:16.580 --> 01:17.830
No.

01:17.830 --> 01:19.420
This is every idea
I gave them

01:19.420 --> 01:21.880
but without the context
and explanation.

01:21.880 --> 01:25.670
I mean, this is gonna
terrify people.

01:25.670 --> 01:28.830
Yeah. I think that's the point,
judging by the headline.

01:28.830 --> 01:31.380
"Hospital Hell
at Grey-Sloan Memorial --

01:31.380 --> 01:33.580
Fired Surgeon
Speaks Out"?

01:33.580 --> 01:35.580
I didn't say that.
I would never say that!

01:35.580 --> 01:37.120
They just made that up.

01:37.120 --> 01:38.380
Yeah, they make
the headlines up.

01:38.380 --> 01:40.620
Amelia:
90,000 likes so far.

01:40.620 --> 01:41.460
You're a hit.

01:41.460 --> 01:42.750
My routine lap appy

01:42.750 --> 01:44.920
was now a case
of multi-organ failure.

01:44.920 --> 01:46.120
Bailey's gonna kill me.

01:46.120 --> 01:47.960
No, Bailey's
gonna kill me.

01:47.960 --> 01:51.540
And there wasn't a damn thing
I could do to stop it.

01:51.540 --> 01:55.750
"In the eyes of the hospital,
you are your insurance."

01:55.750 --> 01:57.250
[ Laughs ]

01:57.250 --> 01:59.380
What? It's funny.
You don't think it's funny?

01:59.380 --> 02:01.250
"Hospital Hell
at Grey-Sloan Memorial"?

02:01.250 --> 02:02.830
This is about
the place that I work.

02:02.830 --> 02:06.080
I offered you a job with me.
You shoulda taken it.

02:06.080 --> 02:07.500
Ow!
[ Laughs ]

02:07.500 --> 02:10.290
[ Foghorn blaring,
seagulls squawking ]

02:13.120 --> 02:14.380
Vic: You know,
walking and texting

02:14.380 --> 02:16.250
is one of the leading causes
of head injury.

02:16.250 --> 02:18.540
Hey.
Hi.

02:18.540 --> 02:20.960
My, uh, colleague --
former colleague --
Mm-hmm.

02:20.960 --> 02:24.580
My friend, uh,
published this list today.

02:24.580 --> 02:27.210
"In America,

02:27.210 --> 02:30.040
the rich live 10 to 15 years
longer than the poor.

02:30.040 --> 02:31.670
The healthcare industry
sells its time

02:31.670 --> 02:32.750
to whoever
can afford it."

02:32.750 --> 02:33.920
Mm.

02:33.920 --> 02:35.420
Damn.
Is that true?

02:35.420 --> 02:36.380
Unfortunately, yeah.

02:36.380 --> 02:37.750
Hmm.

02:37.750 --> 02:39.380
You know,
when a house is on fire,

02:39.380 --> 02:41.960
we just put it out,
no questions, no charge.

02:41.960 --> 02:43.620
Mm-hmm.

02:43.620 --> 02:46.880
But I guess that's why everyone
loves firefighters, huh?

02:46.880 --> 02:49.000
I think
I understand why.

02:49.000 --> 02:50.210
[ Engine starts ]
[ Chuckling ]

02:50.210 --> 02:51.790
See you later.
Stop it.

02:59.120 --> 03:00.750
Hey, man.

03:00.750 --> 03:01.830
Bailey.

03:04.120 --> 03:05.290
Why aren't you
in scrubs?

03:05.290 --> 03:06.790
The rig's
less than a minute out.

03:06.790 --> 03:09.620
Uh, Allison's at my mom's,
and I'm just dropping off Leo.

03:09.620 --> 03:12.170
And?
And I'm on
paternity leave.

03:12.170 --> 03:13.380
[ Siren wailing ]
For how long?

03:13.380 --> 03:16.040
For as long as Koracick's
restraining order lasts.

03:16.040 --> 03:18.580
[ Sighs ]
Koracick!

03:23.080 --> 03:25.670
Yan Huang, 35,
dialysis center patient.

03:25.670 --> 03:28.040
His left A.V. fistula ruptured
while getting access.

03:28.040 --> 03:29.920
Okay, let's get him
a fluid bolus

03:29.920 --> 03:31.040
and another unit
on standby.

03:31.040 --> 03:32.750
Where's the --
Where am I?

03:32.750 --> 03:34.500
Uh, Grey-Sloan Memorial. We're
gonna take good care of you.

03:34.500 --> 03:35.670
Whoa, whoa. Don't --
S-Stop. Stop.

03:35.670 --> 03:37.120
Don't take me out
of this ambulance.

03:37.120 --> 03:39.250
But, sir, we have to repair
your fistula before you --

03:39.250 --> 03:41.580
You take me inside,
and I'll sue!
No, no, no, no!
Don't do that!

03:41.580 --> 03:43.250
Sir, go easy.
You need some help, sir.

03:43.250 --> 03:45.290
Not here!
I've seen that list!

03:45.290 --> 03:46.620
[ Breathing heavily ]
What --

03:46.620 --> 03:48.250
Uh, Pac-North
is closest, okay?

03:48.250 --> 03:49.250
Let's go.
What?! What are you --

03:49.250 --> 03:50.710
Let's go. Let's move.

03:50.710 --> 03:55.420
♪♪

03:55.420 --> 03:57.750
[ Siren wailing ]
What list?!

03:57.750 --> 04:03.620
♪♪

04:03.620 --> 04:04.830
No.

04:04.830 --> 04:06.880
No. No.

04:06.880 --> 04:08.710
No. No!

04:15.120 --> 04:18.920
"Healthcare is a $3.5 trillion
industry for a reason."

04:18.920 --> 04:21.080
"Drug companies aggressively
influence doctors

04:21.080 --> 04:22.420
to write you prescriptions,

04:22.420 --> 04:24.580
which sometimes
make you even sicker."

04:24.580 --> 04:26.170
Is there an explanation
or something

04:26.170 --> 04:27.120
at the end
of the article?

04:27.120 --> 04:28.080
Nope.

04:28.080 --> 04:29.420
It ends
with number 40 --

04:29.420 --> 04:31.380
"Thanks to Big Pharma,
it's cheaper for you

04:31.380 --> 04:33.380
to travel out of the country
to buy the medicine you need

04:33.380 --> 04:35.040
than to get it
in your own hometown."

04:35.040 --> 04:36.960
God, Grey
is such a badass.

04:36.960 --> 04:38.120
[ Laughs ]
She torched this place.

04:38.120 --> 04:39.880
Did you actually read it?

04:39.880 --> 04:41.880
It's about the whole healthcare
system, not this place.

04:41.880 --> 04:43.790
Yeah, no one's gonna
look past that headline.

04:43.790 --> 04:47.000
Ah, well, fortunately for me,
I have Hopkins on my résumé

04:47.000 --> 04:48.380
and Tom Koracick
as a mentor.

04:48.380 --> 04:50.670
Y'all, good luck
getting any jobs after --

04:50.670 --> 04:53.170
Casey: Qadri got a job --
Michigan.

04:54.880 --> 04:57.500
I read the article.
Don't stop on my account.

04:57.500 --> 04:59.620
I-I'm, uh, late for rounds.
I -- I'm gonna...

04:59.620 --> 05:00.710
Yeah.

05:03.670 --> 05:05.040
Don't sweat it, man.

05:05.040 --> 05:06.620
Being liked
is overrated.

05:10.080 --> 05:12.290
[ Siren wailing ]

05:12.290 --> 05:13.790
When the scans come in,
page peds

05:13.790 --> 05:16.080
and call that hospital in
Portland for a family history.

05:16.080 --> 05:18.250
Oh, make sure
you dictate the H&Ps

05:18.250 --> 05:20.170
for all the admissions
last night.

05:20.170 --> 05:22.250
And, uh --
Oh, don't forget to check --

05:22.250 --> 05:24.000
Whoa, okay, it's just --
this is kind of a lot.

05:24.000 --> 05:26.250
Maybe I should
write this down.

05:26.250 --> 05:28.830
Have you seen
this...list?

05:28.830 --> 05:30.120
Yeah.

05:30.120 --> 05:31.210
For once,
it's a lot of horrible press

05:31.210 --> 05:32.380
about someplace
that isn't here.

05:32.380 --> 05:33.880
Bailey must be
losing her mind.

05:33.880 --> 05:36.210
Meredith didn't have to
pull it all down in her wake.

05:36.210 --> 05:37.540
That place raised her!

05:37.540 --> 05:39.580
That place kicked us out.
Whose side are you on?

05:39.580 --> 05:41.250
Ruby: Dr. Karev?

05:41.250 --> 05:43.380
The patient who escaped psych
last night, we found him.

05:43.380 --> 05:44.790
Someone escaped psych?

05:44.790 --> 05:46.120
Yeah. He's fine.

05:46.120 --> 05:47.960
Security got him
before he changed into scrubs.

05:49.790 --> 05:52.710
It's amazing what passes
for good news around here.

05:52.710 --> 05:57.330
♪♪

05:57.330 --> 06:00.460
[ Indistinct talking on P.A. ]

06:00.460 --> 06:01.540
[ Sighs ]

06:01.540 --> 06:03.250
[ Keypad clicking ]

06:06.880 --> 06:08.080
Dr. Bailey. Hi.

06:08.080 --> 06:10.330
Um, I would like to schedule
more ALPPS procedures,

06:10.330 --> 06:11.710
if that's okay with you.

06:11.710 --> 06:14.170
"Not enough residency positions
to train doctors,

06:14.170 --> 06:17.000
and with an aging population
and overwhelmed workforce,

06:17.000 --> 06:18.920
we are stretched too thin, and
patients are paying the price."

06:18.920 --> 06:20.580
So, is that a yes?

06:20.580 --> 06:22.460
Hey, uh, Chief, uh,
some of the residents

06:22.460 --> 06:24.580
are a little confused.
[ Chuckles nervously ]

06:24.580 --> 06:26.880
"There's a nationwide epidemic
of physician burnout,

06:26.880 --> 06:29.080
increasing the risk
of medical error,

06:29.080 --> 06:31.420
lowering
your quality of care,

06:31.420 --> 06:32.750
and costing patients and doctors
their lives."

06:32.750 --> 06:34.460
Wow.

06:34.460 --> 06:36.620
Yeah, she was as confused
as the rest of us, alright?

06:36.620 --> 06:38.420
Oh, really?

06:38.420 --> 06:41.750
Uh, well, she didn't write,
"We doctors are the sick ones.

06:41.750 --> 06:42.960
We have the disease.

06:42.960 --> 06:45.120
The call is coming
from inside the house"?

06:45.120 --> 06:46.830
L-Link was supposed to
be with Qadri,

06:46.830 --> 06:48.460
and Simms was supposed to
have Hunt.

06:48.460 --> 06:50.000
They're all
just a little lost, so --

06:50.000 --> 06:51.580
That sounds like
a chief resident problem.

06:51.580 --> 06:54.330
There is no chief resident.
[ Clears throat ]

06:54.330 --> 06:56.290
Dr. Kang quit
this morning.

06:56.290 --> 06:57.620
Because of this list?

06:57.620 --> 06:58.880
I'm guessing.

06:58.880 --> 07:00.420
[ Sighs ]

07:00.420 --> 07:02.460
Well, congratulations.

07:02.460 --> 07:04.500
You are
my new chief resident.

07:04.500 --> 07:06.290
Maybe you can fix
what your girlfriend broke.

07:06.290 --> 07:08.000
Dr. Bailey, with all
due respect, this is not --

07:08.000 --> 07:10.460
Don't "all due respect" me,
DeLuca.

07:10.460 --> 07:12.420
You had to know
this was coming!

07:12.420 --> 07:14.120
Hey, you work here.

07:14.120 --> 07:16.710
Your career, your future
prospects are all right --

07:16.710 --> 07:19.290
You think I can control
what Meredith Grey writes?

07:19.290 --> 07:20.920
Well, I-I-I think
you could have warned us.

07:20.920 --> 07:22.420
I think you could have
sent up a flare.

07:22.420 --> 07:24.960
I think you could have
had some type of loyalty

07:24.960 --> 07:27.620
to the institution that's
raising you and training you --

07:27.620 --> 07:29.330
Why is it 100 degrees
in here?!

07:29.330 --> 07:31.080
Is it your heart?
Do you need to sit down?

07:34.960 --> 07:37.620
D-Dr. DeLuca, uh...

07:37.620 --> 07:40.080
do you feel this article

07:40.080 --> 07:42.000
is an accurate representation
of our hospital?

07:42.000 --> 07:43.210
No, I do not.

07:43.210 --> 07:45.040
Good. Go. Lead.
Bye!

07:45.040 --> 07:46.790
Okay.

07:46.790 --> 07:49.670
Just keep breathing.
Just keep breathing.

07:49.670 --> 07:54.380
♪♪

07:54.380 --> 07:55.620
Jackson: You want to film
my surgery?

07:55.620 --> 07:56.960
No, absolutely not.

07:56.960 --> 07:59.330
Not sure if you heard, but
a disgruntled former employee

07:59.330 --> 08:01.210
wrote a slash-and-burn exposé
of this place.

08:01.210 --> 08:02.620
It wasn't
about this place.

08:02.620 --> 08:03.830
Headline says otherwise.

08:03.830 --> 08:05.000
Okay,
so, what, your idea

08:05.000 --> 08:06.620
is to throw a camera
in my patient's face?

08:06.620 --> 08:07.880
For Catherine Fox's kid,

08:07.880 --> 08:09.790
it sure takes a long time
for that oven to preheat.

08:09.790 --> 08:11.000
We're in
damage-control mode.

08:11.000 --> 08:12.120
You should be thanking me

08:12.120 --> 08:13.120
for setting all this up
on such short notice.

08:13.120 --> 08:14.670
And yet I'm not, Tom.

08:14.670 --> 08:16.830
This kid's parents
are already blaming themselves

08:16.830 --> 08:19.080
for letting her condition
get this bad, okay?

08:19.080 --> 08:20.460
A little kid
is not a spectacle.

08:20.460 --> 08:22.250
I know. She's a beautiful
little miracle,

08:22.250 --> 08:24.460
and you are the angelic,
camera-ready plastic surgeon

08:24.460 --> 08:25.920
who's gonna
make her all better.

08:25.920 --> 08:27.000
It's a win-win.

08:27.000 --> 08:29.040
[ Pats ]

08:29.040 --> 08:30.710
Koracick:
Mr. and Mrs. Martin.

08:30.710 --> 08:33.790
And you must be
Clervie.

08:33.790 --> 08:35.420
Come on in, Dr. Avery.

08:36.540 --> 08:38.290
There.

08:38.290 --> 08:40.330
[ Chuckles ]

08:40.330 --> 08:42.250
Excuse me.
Hi. Dr. Avery.

08:42.250 --> 08:44.170
Hi. Nice to meet you.
How are you?

08:44.170 --> 08:46.170
Hello.
How you doing?

08:46.170 --> 08:47.960
Good.
Yeah?

08:47.960 --> 08:49.670
They just shaved my head.
Alright.

08:49.670 --> 08:52.210
We're gonna take
really good care of you, okay?

08:52.210 --> 08:54.790
Our patient
fell from a plane?

08:54.790 --> 08:57.080
No. A person fell from a plane
and hit another person.

08:57.080 --> 09:00.210
Oof. Sounds like
what Dr. Grey did to Big Pharma.

09:00.210 --> 09:02.040
Oh, my God.
How is he alive?

09:02.040 --> 09:03.880
Alicia Chen, 19, GCS 8,

09:03.880 --> 09:05.750
with bilateral
lower-extremity deformities,

09:05.750 --> 09:06.920
possible pelvic fracture.

09:06.920 --> 09:08.960
Saw some ST elevation
on her EKG.

09:08.960 --> 09:10.750
Josh: We were just hanging out
outside my dorm,

09:10.750 --> 09:13.120
and he f-fell
from the sky.

09:13.120 --> 09:14.540
Alright,
page cardio and ortho.

09:14.540 --> 09:15.920
Let's get her
in trauma one.

09:15.920 --> 09:17.380
Is Alicia --
Is she dead?

09:17.380 --> 09:18.540
Sir, what's your name?

09:18.540 --> 09:20.460
It's Josh. I'm Josh.
Hey, Josh.

09:20.460 --> 09:21.710
Alright, you know what?
You need to stay here.

09:21.710 --> 09:23.540
We're gonna assess your friend
and take good care of her.

09:23.540 --> 09:25.420
Why isn't he on a gurney?
He's obviously bleeding.

09:25.420 --> 09:26.790
It's not his.
It belongs to the guy who fell.

09:26.790 --> 09:28.540
He just exploded
all over us.

09:28.540 --> 09:29.920
Okay, look,
why don't you...

09:29.920 --> 09:31.500
Alright, on my count --
1, 2, 3.

09:31.500 --> 09:32.500
Go.

09:39.170 --> 09:41.040
[ Foghorn blaring,
seagulls squawking ]

09:41.040 --> 09:44.000
Well, change the headline
at least!

09:44.000 --> 09:46.250
I love Grey-Sloan.
I own Grey-Sloan.

09:46.250 --> 09:47.960
I wouldn't write anything
to tear it down.

09:47.960 --> 09:49.580
I don't really care

09:49.580 --> 09:51.580
if it's the most shared piece
of the month.

09:51.580 --> 09:53.620
The headline is so misleading!

09:57.580 --> 10:00.290
Well, run it up the flagpole
quickly, please!

10:02.080 --> 10:09.880
♪♪

10:09.880 --> 10:11.170
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

10:11.170 --> 10:14.250
In cases
of craniosyno...stosis,

10:14.250 --> 10:16.670
the -- the structures
of the skull fuse too early,

10:16.670 --> 10:20.420
resulting in abnormal growth
and...development.

10:20.420 --> 10:22.040
Well, what we'll
be doing today

10:22.040 --> 10:25.830
is carefully removing
the top of Clervie's skull,

10:25.830 --> 10:27.080
break apart the bone,

10:27.080 --> 10:29.380
and use those pieces
to re-shape her skull,

10:29.380 --> 10:31.080
allowing everything
to fit perfectly

10:31.080 --> 10:33.620
and have plenty of room to grow
just the right way.

10:33.620 --> 10:35.960
Our pediatrician said
it was just a mild case

10:35.960 --> 10:37.170
and she would outgrow it.

10:37.170 --> 10:39.210
Peter: It just kept growing
and getting worse,

10:39.210 --> 10:40.580
and now it's --

10:40.580 --> 10:44.000
It's more dangerous, right,
now that she's older?

10:44.000 --> 10:45.790
Well, it's slightly
more complicated,

10:45.790 --> 10:48.290
but, honestly, it's absolutely
nothing we can't handle.

10:48.290 --> 10:50.330
What's important
is that you're here now.

10:50.330 --> 10:52.830
We're gonna take great care
of your little girl, I promise.

10:52.830 --> 10:54.460
When Dr. Koracick
called this morning

10:54.460 --> 10:57.330
and said you could do
the surgery for free --

10:57.330 --> 10:58.960
I mean...

10:58.960 --> 11:02.170
you hate to have to think
about money with your child,

11:02.170 --> 11:05.250
but we were gonna have to
take out a second mortgage.

11:05.250 --> 11:06.880
Thank you.

11:09.040 --> 11:11.170
Yeah, th-- it's our --
it's our pleasure.

11:15.880 --> 11:17.830
You were born
for the camera, Avery.

11:17.830 --> 11:19.540
Schmitt, baby steps.

11:19.540 --> 11:21.580
You bribed
desperate parents

11:21.580 --> 11:24.500
so you can use their fear
and pain for cheap publicity?

11:24.500 --> 11:25.880
Finally,
Wonder Boy gets it.

11:25.880 --> 11:27.420
Wow.

11:27.420 --> 11:29.830
Just when I thought I couldn't
possibly like you less,

11:29.830 --> 11:31.540
you surprise me.

11:31.540 --> 11:34.040
Hey, now, give them some space
but not too much.

11:34.040 --> 11:35.750
And remember, anyone prays,
get that on camera.

11:35.750 --> 11:36.750
That is gold.
[ Scoffs ]

11:36.750 --> 11:38.710
And you did it again.
Impressive.

11:38.710 --> 11:39.710
Wha--

11:40.960 --> 11:42.580
Uh, you --

11:44.710 --> 11:46.670
[ Breathing heavily ]

11:46.670 --> 11:48.290
Hey. You.

11:48.290 --> 11:50.330
We need to skip the E.R.
Page your head of vascular.

11:50.330 --> 11:51.460
We don't have one.

11:51.460 --> 11:52.710
Well, then page Karev
or Webber.

11:52.710 --> 11:54.120
I'm gonna hand him off
in the O.R.

11:54.120 --> 11:55.830
Right. Okay.

11:57.540 --> 11:59.040
Hey, I don't know
where your O.R. is!

11:59.040 --> 12:00.620
[ Receiver clicks ]

12:00.620 --> 12:01.500
Let's go.

12:04.250 --> 12:05.920
Hey, hey! It's good
to see a friendly face.

12:05.920 --> 12:07.460
Webber. Great.

12:07.460 --> 12:11.040
Dialysis patient, 35, uh,
ruptured left A.V. fistula,

12:11.040 --> 12:12.420
lost a good amount
of blood

12:12.420 --> 12:14.290
and refused treatment
at Grey-Sloan.

12:14.290 --> 12:15.290
Refused treatment?
Mm-hmm.

12:15.290 --> 12:16.420
Did you read this list?

12:16.420 --> 12:18.000
I'm glad
nobody wrote about us.

12:18.000 --> 12:19.750
Hey, hey, hey, hey!
Come here.

12:19.750 --> 12:21.380
Get this man
to O.R. 4,

12:21.380 --> 12:24.080
and if you can keep your mouth
shut, you can scrub in with me.

12:24.080 --> 12:25.290
Thanks for
the business, Hunt.
Sure.

12:25.290 --> 12:26.750
[ Indistinct talking on P.A. ]

12:26.750 --> 12:28.710
Okay.

12:28.710 --> 12:30.120
Hey, man.

12:30.120 --> 12:32.170
Hey.
Bailey send you
to spy on me?

12:32.170 --> 12:34.500
[ Chuckles ] No, no.
I'm just dropping off a patient.

12:34.500 --> 12:36.080
I'm, uh,
taking some time off.

12:37.830 --> 12:40.000
Koracick is
driving me insane,

12:40.000 --> 12:42.830
so Teddy's taking over
the E.R.,

12:42.830 --> 12:44.580
and I'm staying home
with the kids for a while.

12:44.580 --> 12:45.880
Well, if you don't
have to rush home,

12:45.880 --> 12:47.290
I'd love to --
to give you a tour.

12:47.290 --> 12:48.500
Sure.

12:48.500 --> 12:50.500
Well, you have to use
your imagination, you know?

12:50.500 --> 12:54.120
Try to picture it with, uh,
new lighting, paint job,

12:54.120 --> 12:57.830
a few new walls,
qualified medical personnel.

12:57.830 --> 12:59.880
Pelvis X-ray shows a type II
A.P. compression fracture.

12:59.880 --> 13:01.120
Where did she fall from?

13:01.120 --> 13:02.710
The guy fell on her.

13:02.710 --> 13:04.750
Cops think he was a stowaway
on an international flight.

13:06.000 --> 13:07.330
Teddy:
Helm, get the ultrasound.

13:07.330 --> 13:09.290
Reminds me
of a guy in Germany

13:09.290 --> 13:12.420
who snuck into the wheel well
of a 757.

13:12.420 --> 13:15.120
All was fine and good until
they hit cruising altitude.

13:15.120 --> 13:16.500
What happened
at cruising altitude?

13:16.500 --> 13:19.750
It's colder than Everest,
and there's less O2.

13:19.750 --> 13:21.750
Brody, let's order some,
uh, bilateral leg films.

13:21.750 --> 13:23.540
And when
the landing gear opens,

13:23.540 --> 13:26.330
it's like dropping an ice pack
on the ground from a mile high.

13:26.330 --> 13:28.000
But the ice pack is made of
blood and muscle tissue,

13:28.000 --> 13:30.000
so -- pbht! -- splat.

13:30.000 --> 13:32.790
Hughes. Hello.
What do we got?

13:32.790 --> 13:35.580
19-year-old,
bilateral tib-fib fractures,

13:35.580 --> 13:37.170
unstable pelvic fracture.

13:37.170 --> 13:38.670
And the X-rays
show that --

13:38.670 --> 13:41.040
Widened mediastinum,
sternal fracture.

13:41.040 --> 13:42.460
What's the ultrasound?

13:42.460 --> 13:43.670
Uh...

13:43.670 --> 13:44.750
Turn on the color flow.

13:45.960 --> 13:48.580
Looks like
severe aortic insufficiency.

13:48.580 --> 13:52.000
EKG showed ST elevations
in leads II, III, and AVF.

13:52.000 --> 13:55.670
Could be ischemic changes
secondary to aortic root injury.

13:55.670 --> 13:57.000
Alright,
her pressure looks stable.

13:57.000 --> 13:58.380
Let's get a CTA
to get a better look.

13:58.380 --> 14:00.420
Yeah, seems like
you guys got this covered.

14:00.420 --> 14:02.750
Link: Alright, as soon
as I finish getting this
binder on, you can move her.

14:02.750 --> 14:04.580
Hannah: I think that's her
boyfriend out there panicking.

14:04.580 --> 14:07.670
There you go. She's good.
I'll go check on him.

14:07.670 --> 14:10.000
Pierce is kind of a genius,
isn't she?

14:10.000 --> 14:12.250
[ Chuckles ]
Not kind of. Is.

14:12.250 --> 14:14.170
Hey, um,
we got a few minutes?

14:14.170 --> 14:15.170
I need to go talk
to my wife.

14:15.170 --> 14:16.540
Oh, is it about
that list?

14:16.540 --> 14:17.830
Avery told me.

14:17.830 --> 14:20.080
Yeah.
It's about that list.

14:21.080 --> 14:22.670
Now, what's
your name, bud?

14:22.670 --> 14:25.540
Josh.
Alright.

14:25.540 --> 14:27.170
Alright, that accident must have
been tough to see, huh?

14:27.170 --> 14:28.380
[ Breathing heavily ]
Yeah.

14:28.380 --> 14:30.790
I'm gonna do a little exam,
okay?

14:30.790 --> 14:33.920
Alright, Josh, hey,
those two doctors in there,

14:33.920 --> 14:35.120
they don't
make them any better.

14:35.120 --> 14:36.380
Your girlfriend --

14:36.380 --> 14:38.500
Ali-- Alicia.
Alicia.

14:38.500 --> 14:41.040
They're gonna do everything
they can to help Alicia.

14:41.040 --> 14:43.040
Alright,
you hear me, Josh?

14:43.040 --> 14:44.540
Can you take a deep breath
for me?

14:44.540 --> 14:46.080
[ Breathing deeply ]

14:52.080 --> 14:53.670
Okay. Good.

14:53.670 --> 14:55.380
Alright, we're gonna
clean you up

14:55.380 --> 14:57.420
and, uh, get you something
to help you calm down.

14:57.420 --> 14:59.250
Are you currently taking
any prescrip--

15:03.830 --> 15:05.250
Where did you get that?

15:07.330 --> 15:08.710
My hood.

15:08.710 --> 15:09.960
I tell you what, um,

15:09.960 --> 15:12.790
I'm gonna get you some
clean scrubs to change into,

15:12.790 --> 15:15.210
and while I'm at it,
I'm just gonna...

15:21.960 --> 15:24.790
Hi. Lisa, is it?

15:24.790 --> 15:28.000
Hi. So, I did, um, both sides
of the street up to 1st Avenue

15:28.000 --> 15:29.790
and then
the parking lot.

15:29.790 --> 15:31.330
I don't give out
gold stars.

15:31.330 --> 15:32.830
Head back over
across the street.

15:32.830 --> 15:34.500
There's a lot of empties
over there.

15:34.500 --> 15:36.790
Actually, so,
I have an emergency,

15:36.790 --> 15:38.670
and I-I really need to go.

15:38.670 --> 15:41.750
Grey, I know all about you
and your emergencies.

15:41.750 --> 15:44.380
I wrote something, and -- and
it's been taken out of context.

15:44.380 --> 15:47.250
The headline has actually
nothing to do with what I said,

15:47.250 --> 15:49.460
and I need to go
take care of it.
You have five more hours
for today.

15:49.460 --> 15:51.790
Lisa.

15:51.790 --> 15:53.920
Human to human.

15:56.620 --> 15:58.830
It's a real emergency
for me.

15:58.830 --> 16:01.250
I really need to go
take care of this.

16:01.250 --> 16:03.420
You walk away
before your time's up,

16:03.420 --> 16:05.670
I'm calling the judge about
all your extracurriculars.

16:05.670 --> 16:06.920
You decide.

16:06.920 --> 16:08.500
[ Cellphone chimes ]

16:08.500 --> 16:13.170
♪♪

16:13.170 --> 16:15.830
Please don't call the judge.
I will make up my hours.

16:15.830 --> 16:17.330
I have to go.

16:17.330 --> 16:18.460
Please don't call him.

16:18.460 --> 16:21.080
I promise
I'll make up the hours.

16:21.080 --> 16:22.880
Grey!

16:22.880 --> 16:24.120
Grey?!

16:29.750 --> 16:32.330
Well, Mer's list
really freed up my morning.

16:32.330 --> 16:33.920
I've had two surgeries
cancel.

16:33.920 --> 16:34.960
Are you mad?

16:34.960 --> 16:37.000
Mm. A little.

16:37.000 --> 16:39.540
But I never win fights with her,
even inside my head,

16:39.540 --> 16:41.420
so I'm just
shoving it down.

16:41.420 --> 16:42.250
Mm.

16:42.250 --> 16:43.330
Have you seen Link?

16:43.330 --> 16:45.420
I'm craving
some gravity blanket.

16:45.420 --> 16:46.710
What?

16:46.710 --> 16:48.210
Oh, we used to
do this thing

16:48.210 --> 16:50.330
where he would just put all
of his body weight on top of me,

16:50.330 --> 16:52.460
and it was like a thunder jacket
for a dog.

16:52.460 --> 16:55.120
But now I've got the little
peanut, so he just bear-hugs me.

16:55.120 --> 16:57.170
I'm claustrophobic. I can't
think of anything less soothing.

16:57.170 --> 16:58.830
But sounds like
you two are a match.

16:58.830 --> 17:00.420
We kind of are,
aren't we?

17:00.420 --> 17:02.120
I mean,
I get all spinny-outy,

17:02.120 --> 17:05.960
and he's just like
a big, calm mountain.

17:05.960 --> 17:08.120
Well, uh,
right now your mountain

17:08.120 --> 17:10.290
is trying to calm down
my patient's boyfriend.

17:10.290 --> 17:11.920
What happened
to your patient?
[ Sighs ]

17:11.920 --> 17:13.250
Just imagine --

17:13.250 --> 17:14.420
Never mind.
Don't imagine.

17:14.420 --> 17:17.380
Pierce!
I need a word.

17:17.380 --> 17:19.040
Okay. Uh, if this is
about Mer's list,

17:19.040 --> 17:20.460
I don't want to hear it.

17:20.460 --> 17:22.620
I stand by her as a surgeon
and as a sister.

17:22.620 --> 17:24.290
I don't care.
Follow me, please.

17:24.290 --> 17:28.920
♪♪

17:28.920 --> 17:31.540
And just need one last sample
to confirm blood type

17:31.540 --> 17:32.750
in case there's any bleeding
in the O.R.

17:32.750 --> 17:33.750
Otherwise,
we'll be fine.

17:33.750 --> 17:34.830
Thank you so much.

17:37.250 --> 17:41.080
She really is just
such a happy little girl.

17:41.080 --> 17:42.960
We've learned so much
from her,

17:42.960 --> 17:45.710
and we feel so blessed
to have --

17:45.710 --> 17:47.880
to have met the doctors here
so she can...

17:47.880 --> 17:50.120
[ Clears throat,
chuckles ]

17:50.120 --> 17:52.250
...so she can get
the help that she needs.

17:52.250 --> 17:54.170
This is no good.
Too much backlight.

17:54.170 --> 17:55.790
Oh, uh...

17:55.790 --> 17:57.880
Uh, Peter, uh, sorry.

17:57.880 --> 17:59.380
Uh, technical stuff.

17:59.380 --> 18:00.380
You okay?

18:00.380 --> 18:01.790
Yeah.
Yeah. Okay.

18:01.790 --> 18:03.830
Uh, we're gonna get you to,
uh, say that again,

18:03.830 --> 18:05.500
I mean, just --
just like you did

18:05.500 --> 18:09.040
but just a little bit more,
uh, over here.

18:09.040 --> 18:10.580
Yeah.
Alright.

18:10.580 --> 18:11.790
Okay.
Actually,
you know what, Peter?

18:11.790 --> 18:14.330
I think it was perfect.
There's no need.

18:14.330 --> 18:15.420
Take a break.

18:17.790 --> 18:18.830
You know what?

18:18.830 --> 18:20.670
Dr. Avery is right

18:20.670 --> 18:22.710
'cause we need to talk
to Mrs. Martin anyway.

18:22.710 --> 18:24.380
So...yeah.

18:24.380 --> 18:26.000
Yeah.

18:26.000 --> 18:27.080
Thank you, guys.

18:33.420 --> 18:35.210
This man is in fear,
right, real fear.

18:35.210 --> 18:36.750
His daughter's
3 years old.

18:36.750 --> 18:39.250
This surgery's gonna
be traumatic, painful,
and life-threatening,

18:39.250 --> 18:43.170
and you need him to say it all
again with better lighting?

18:43.170 --> 18:45.460
Dr. Avery, I don't think
you need to be reminded,

18:45.460 --> 18:48.290
but just in case,
I am your boss.

18:48.290 --> 18:50.620
If you need more clarification
on the matter, lemme know,

18:50.620 --> 18:54.420
and I can have your mom call
and explain it to you.

18:54.420 --> 18:56.040
Oh.

18:56.040 --> 18:57.710
Well, while you have her,
ask her how much longer

18:57.710 --> 18:59.830
she's gonna be punishing us
with you.

18:59.830 --> 19:02.540
[ Chuckles ]
Ah, funny.

19:02.540 --> 19:04.500
No chest pain,
no shortness of breath.

19:04.500 --> 19:07.330
Your EKG
shows no changes.

19:07.330 --> 19:11.080
I see no arrhythmias
or abnormal flow.

19:11.080 --> 19:12.620
So Grey didn't give me
a heart attack.

19:12.620 --> 19:13.790
No.

19:13.790 --> 19:15.040
You're just warm.

19:15.040 --> 19:17.790
War-- [ Scoffs ]
I'm in a sauna.

19:17.790 --> 19:20.000
How long
has it been like this?

19:20.000 --> 19:22.290
A few days?
I don't know, Pierce.

19:22.290 --> 19:23.540
[ Exhales sharply ]

19:23.540 --> 19:26.380
Uh, you know,
I got a lot on my mind,

19:26.380 --> 19:28.960
and this list isn't
making it any better.

19:28.960 --> 19:30.620
Well,
it's not your heart.

19:30.620 --> 19:31.830
Well, what is it?

19:31.830 --> 19:33.500
[ Sighs ]

19:33.500 --> 19:35.920
It could be hor--
It could be hormonal.

19:39.920 --> 19:41.330
I have to be in surgery
in 15 minutes,

19:41.330 --> 19:43.250
but I could do
a quick blood draw

19:43.250 --> 19:44.670
and, uh,
check your levels?

19:44.670 --> 19:46.670
Okay, well, do it right quick,
then, if you have to go.

19:46.670 --> 19:49.460
I-I need a full blood panel,
CBC, thyroid --

19:49.460 --> 19:51.920
Yeah, I know how to do
a blood panel.

19:54.380 --> 19:56.380
Schmitt, uh,
where are we with, uh, cran--

19:56.380 --> 19:57.750
Mom, no.

19:57.750 --> 19:59.920
Tell Aunt Carol
she doesn't need

19:59.920 --> 20:01.500
to reschedule
her carpal tunnel surgery.

20:01.500 --> 20:03.040
We're still
a good hospital.

20:03.040 --> 20:04.880
[ Clears throat ]

20:04.880 --> 20:07.920
I-I-I'm at work right now.
I have to go.

20:07.920 --> 20:09.580
Sorry.

20:09.580 --> 20:12.460
My mom sent Grey's article
to everyone in our family,

20:12.460 --> 20:14.710
and they gave me the money
for med school,

20:14.710 --> 20:16.460
so they're very invested.

20:16.460 --> 20:18.120
You're on the phone,
and you're not doing your job.

20:18.120 --> 20:19.670
You're basically a bullet point
on Grey's list.

20:19.670 --> 20:20.750
Get back to work.

20:20.750 --> 20:22.580
[ Sighs heavily ]

20:22.580 --> 20:25.120
I sent a proposal to
the board to see if
they'll expand the NICU.

20:25.120 --> 20:26.210
I swear, this place
must be backed

20:26.210 --> 20:27.380
by Russian Mafia
or something

20:27.380 --> 20:28.830
because they are not afraid
to write checks.

20:28.830 --> 20:30.000
That doesn't hurt.

20:30.000 --> 20:31.830
Over here, I want to,
uh, put in

20:31.830 --> 20:34.620
the new innovative pediatric
surgery unit by spring.

20:34.620 --> 20:36.330
You know, this place
is really shaping up.

20:36.330 --> 20:37.380
[ Woman screams ]

20:37.380 --> 20:39.540
Oh, my God!
Somebody, help!

20:39.540 --> 20:42.460
Miller, what happened?
Doug:
Patient just had colon surgery
due to a perforation.

20:42.460 --> 20:44.790
His wound vac started filling
with blood and -- I don't know.

20:44.790 --> 20:46.580
Did you send blood
for a coag panel? Hmm?

20:47.830 --> 20:49.500
Ma'am, I need you
to stand back now, please.

20:49.500 --> 20:50.710
[ Woman whimpers ]

20:50.710 --> 20:52.500
I feel warm.

20:52.500 --> 20:53.710
Woman:
Why won't it stop?!

20:53.710 --> 20:55.120
Karev, is it okay
if I jump in?

20:55.120 --> 20:56.170
Yeah, please.
What do you need?

20:56.170 --> 20:57.420
Okay.

20:57.420 --> 20:59.170
You, get me a crash cart,

20:59.170 --> 21:01.580
two units of blood, gauze,
and suction, okay?

21:03.170 --> 21:04.250
Now!

21:04.250 --> 21:06.000
See what I have to
put up with?

21:06.000 --> 21:07.000
[ Sighs ]

21:07.000 --> 21:08.620
[ Monitor beeping ]

21:08.620 --> 21:11.120
[ Door opens ]

21:11.120 --> 21:14.170
Ohh! I've had a really crazy
day, and I can't really talk.

21:14.170 --> 21:16.330
I thought you might be
in the E.R.,

21:16.330 --> 21:19.500
seeing as how a body just fell
from the [Laughing] sky.

21:19.500 --> 21:21.250
I mean, I've never
seen anything like it,

21:21.250 --> 21:22.790
I mean,
I've seen some things.

21:22.790 --> 21:24.170
[ Groans ]

21:25.710 --> 21:27.170
[ Sniffles ]
Okay, Miranda, look,

21:27.170 --> 21:29.170
if -- if you're still upset
about Grey's list --

21:29.170 --> 21:31.170
But, hey,
it'll blow over, alright?

21:31.170 --> 21:34.040
Try not to make yourself more
angry by staring at it all day.

21:34.040 --> 21:35.920
That's not why I'm angry.

21:35.920 --> 21:37.210
It's -- It's not?

21:37.210 --> 21:39.710
I'm angry because
it's 1,000 degrees in here,

21:39.710 --> 21:41.120
and I can't stop crying

21:41.120 --> 21:43.920
because my hormones are
hitting me like a tidal wave

21:43.920 --> 21:46.670
because I am
in menopause!

21:46.670 --> 21:48.080
Miranda, we don't --
No!

21:48.080 --> 21:50.500
Don't bother telling me
that that's not what it is,

21:50.500 --> 21:53.170
because I saw it happen
to my mom at a young age,

21:53.170 --> 21:55.330
and now it's happening
to me.

21:55.330 --> 21:57.670
And I know it's
the natural order of things.

21:57.670 --> 22:00.250
I am woman.
Hear me roar.

22:00.250 --> 22:02.620
I knew it was coming...

22:02.620 --> 22:04.580
someday!

22:05.790 --> 22:07.750
I'm sorry, Ben.

22:09.460 --> 22:14.790
No one really warns you
about all the feelings.

22:14.790 --> 22:17.170
[ Sobbing ]

22:21.420 --> 22:23.210
Just tell me
what you need.

22:24.540 --> 22:26.330
[ Sniffles ]
Just -- Here.

22:26.330 --> 22:29.290
Just sit here with me
for like five minutes

22:29.290 --> 22:34.830
and let me have
all the feelings.

22:36.670 --> 22:39.750
Oh, God! Stupid.

22:39.750 --> 22:41.210
[ Gasping heavily ]

22:41.210 --> 22:42.540
Okay, okay.
It's hot!

22:49.040 --> 22:51.000
[ Indistinct talking on P.A. ]

22:51.000 --> 22:52.000
[ Light thud ]

22:52.000 --> 22:53.120
Hey!

22:55.120 --> 22:56.790
How bad is it?

22:56.790 --> 22:59.620
Okay. Well, um,
residents are panicking.

22:59.620 --> 23:01.120
Everyone else
seems split.

23:01.120 --> 23:03.040
Some are pissed.
Some are calling you a hero.

23:03.040 --> 23:04.670
Alex couldn't stop laughing
all morning.

23:04.670 --> 23:06.290
Where do you land?

23:06.290 --> 23:08.170
Well, I wish you hadn't
name-checked the hospital

23:08.170 --> 23:09.540
that just made me
an attending,

23:09.540 --> 23:11.880
but I think it'll start
some much-needed conversation

23:11.880 --> 23:13.830
once tempers calm.

23:13.830 --> 23:15.170
Like Bailey's temper?

23:15.170 --> 23:17.380
Okay, her rage level
is so high,

23:17.380 --> 23:18.620
I'm worried
for her physical health.

23:18.620 --> 23:21.500
Well, I would like to explain
how this happened.

23:21.500 --> 23:23.380
Especially to Bailey.
I owe it to her.

23:23.380 --> 23:24.790
I mean,
I named my kid after her.

23:24.790 --> 23:26.420
She might ask you
to take that back.

23:26.420 --> 23:28.080
Um --
Good luck.

23:28.080 --> 23:29.880
[ Indistinct talking on P.A. ]

23:32.210 --> 23:34.080
There. You see that?
That's the source of the bleed.

23:34.080 --> 23:35.670
The aorta.
The aorta?

23:35.670 --> 23:37.670
No. What year are you?
Second.

23:37.670 --> 23:38.830
[ Groans ]

23:38.830 --> 23:40.250
Superior
epigastric artery.

23:40.250 --> 23:42.170
One of the cardinal rules
in trauma

23:42.170 --> 23:43.960
is to find the source
of the bleeding and...?

23:43.960 --> 23:47.040
Uh...
Get proximal
and distal control.

23:47.040 --> 23:49.380
Okay, looks like poor hemostasis
after surgery.

23:49.380 --> 23:52.250
Let's get him in the O.R. and do
a repair and a quick washout.

23:52.250 --> 23:53.880
Alright. Miller,
book the next available O.R.

23:53.880 --> 23:55.120
for Dr. Hunt right now.

23:55.120 --> 23:56.500
Right.
Um, who's Dr. Hunt?

23:56.500 --> 23:57.790
Him.
Me.

23:57.790 --> 23:58.880
Okay.

23:58.880 --> 24:02.380
♪♪

24:02.380 --> 24:04.790
Alright, page me
when Clervie's ready.

24:04.790 --> 24:07.210
Try not to trip
on any camera wires.

24:07.210 --> 24:08.580
Cameras?

24:08.580 --> 24:11.500
Yeah, doing a craniosynostosis
on a 3-year-old,

24:11.500 --> 24:13.620
which Koracick is
turning into a feel-good video

24:13.620 --> 24:15.920
so he could fight the bad
attention around Mer's list.

24:15.920 --> 24:18.670
Also, he bribed the family
with a pro bono surgery.

24:18.670 --> 24:19.920
Ew. Gross.

24:19.920 --> 24:22.040
And yet
totally on brand.

24:22.040 --> 24:24.380
[ Sighs ]
Meredith's kind of lucky,
when you think about it.

24:24.380 --> 24:26.790
Uh, losing her job
and possibly losing her license?

24:26.790 --> 24:28.250
Well, I mean,
yeah, obviously,

24:28.250 --> 24:30.120
but she doesn't have to
worry about all this crap,

24:30.120 --> 24:31.380
you know,
how things look.

24:31.380 --> 24:34.120
She can just...
do the right thing.

24:36.170 --> 24:37.790
I love a good dare.

24:37.790 --> 24:39.120
That wasn't a dare.
Thank you.

24:39.120 --> 24:40.790
Wait. No. I don't really think
that she's lucky!

24:42.210 --> 24:44.170
[ Monitor beeping,
suction gurgling ]

24:46.670 --> 24:47.830
Maggie: Good to be back?

24:47.830 --> 24:50.580
You have no idea.

24:50.580 --> 24:52.790
But I love
being a mom, too.

24:52.790 --> 24:54.380
No judgment here.

24:54.380 --> 24:56.500
Meredith calls bowel resections
her "me time."

24:56.500 --> 24:58.580
[ Chuckles ]

24:58.580 --> 25:00.460
Taryn:
Would you be willing to tell her
how much I loved her article?

25:00.460 --> 25:03.420
Um, yeah...
Helm, sure.

25:03.420 --> 25:07.210
How amazing and important
and just perfect it is?

25:07.210 --> 25:08.420
And that
she's still my mentor,

25:08.420 --> 25:09.670
even if she doesn't
work here anymore?

25:09.670 --> 25:11.250
I will pass it along.

25:11.250 --> 25:13.880
Alright,
clamping the aorta.

25:13.880 --> 25:15.420
Alright.

25:15.420 --> 25:18.330
We are gonna stop the heart
with cardioplegia

25:18.330 --> 25:20.210
so we can replace
the aortic root.

25:20.210 --> 25:22.540
That's...weird.

25:22.540 --> 25:24.580
The heart's not stopping.
[ Door opens ]

25:24.580 --> 25:26.710
How is she? Finally got
her boyfriend calmed down.

25:26.710 --> 25:27.920
Well, it looks like
the blunt injury

25:27.920 --> 25:30.670
also caused
a coronary artery dissection,

25:30.670 --> 25:32.790
so we're gonna have to
pass the cardioplegia

25:32.790 --> 25:35.670
through the coronary sinus so
we can get this heart to stop.

25:35.670 --> 25:37.380
She cannot
catch a break.

25:37.380 --> 25:39.210
How can I help?
Alright, well, we're gonna
have to do a bypass,

25:39.210 --> 25:42.120
so you can harvest a vein
from her leg

25:42.120 --> 25:43.920
while Pierce and I --
[ Monitors beeping rapidly ]

25:43.920 --> 25:45.080
No! Start pressors!
Crap.

25:45.080 --> 25:46.580
The root is rupturing!

25:46.580 --> 25:48.210
-I'm gonna go scrub.
-Yep.

25:48.210 --> 25:50.170
Get that suction in there.
Get that suction in there.

25:50.170 --> 25:51.620
[ Suction gurgling ]

25:51.620 --> 25:53.290
[ Sighs ]

25:53.290 --> 25:55.330
Hey. You busy?

25:55.330 --> 25:57.420
I just did
a cervical decompression.

25:57.420 --> 25:59.830
Now I'm gonna grab enough lunch
for multiple humans.

25:59.830 --> 26:02.460
I can buy you something from
the vending machine on the way.

26:02.460 --> 26:04.250
On the way to where?

26:05.710 --> 26:07.880
Jackson: Don't worry.
We'll remain right on schedule.

26:07.880 --> 26:10.210
You don't want Dr. Koracick
to operate?

26:10.210 --> 26:13.420
My sister texted us an article
about this hospital.

26:13.420 --> 26:15.330
Is that what this is about?
Is he part of the problem?

26:15.330 --> 26:16.540
No, absolutely not.

26:16.540 --> 26:19.540
No. Tom Koracick is
a brilliant neurosurgeon.

26:19.540 --> 26:21.290
Then why make
a change?

26:21.290 --> 26:23.580
Well, for starters,
I'm better.

26:23.580 --> 26:26.170
Dana, Peter, I know
that you only agreed

26:26.170 --> 26:28.120
to let Tom film the surgery
so it would be free,

26:28.120 --> 26:29.830
but I can...see now

26:29.830 --> 26:32.040
that you're both
a little uncomfortable.

26:32.040 --> 26:34.580
And I can't blame you.
This is a very big decision.

26:34.580 --> 26:36.120
It's your family's
privacy.

26:36.120 --> 26:37.920
You shouldn't have to
think about that

26:37.920 --> 26:39.290
under these conditions.

26:39.290 --> 26:41.460
So, I want you to know that
no matter what happens today,

26:41.460 --> 26:43.290
no matter
what you decide,

26:43.290 --> 26:44.960
your surgery's not gonna
cost you a thing.

26:46.250 --> 26:47.290
Yeah.

26:47.290 --> 26:49.290
W-Why --
Why would you do this?

26:49.290 --> 26:51.330
Well, I have a little girl
of my own,

26:51.330 --> 26:53.250
and if she needed a surgery,
I'd want to make sure

26:53.250 --> 26:54.790
that her doctors
aren't thinking about anything

26:54.790 --> 26:56.330
except for her.

26:56.330 --> 26:58.210
Your little girl
means more to me

26:58.210 --> 26:59.790
than some --
some good press.

26:59.790 --> 27:03.830
♪♪

27:03.830 --> 27:05.580
[ Sighs ]

27:05.580 --> 27:06.380
Yes.

27:07.960 --> 27:09.380
Yes.
And thank you.

27:09.380 --> 27:10.830
Alright.
Let's get going, then.

27:10.830 --> 27:12.580
Alright, guys,
let's come on in.

27:12.580 --> 27:13.880
Thank you so much.

27:17.250 --> 27:18.920
You know
Tom is gonna blow a gasket

27:18.920 --> 27:19.750
when he hears about this.

27:19.750 --> 27:21.120
Oh, I know.

27:21.120 --> 27:22.080
Added bonus.

27:28.290 --> 27:30.420
[ Flatline ]

27:30.420 --> 27:31.380
No.

27:32.580 --> 27:35.380
Time of death 16:04.

27:35.380 --> 27:37.000
Injury was just --
[ Click, flatline stops ]

27:37.000 --> 27:38.880
it caused
too much damage.

27:38.880 --> 27:40.460
Damn it.

27:40.460 --> 27:42.330
It's not just the medical system
that's broken.

27:42.330 --> 27:43.880
It's the whole world.

27:43.880 --> 27:46.670
Why'd the stowaway have to
fall out of a plane?

27:46.670 --> 27:48.000
And how bad was his life

27:48.000 --> 27:49.710
that he had to climb
in the plane to begin with?

27:49.710 --> 27:52.420
And why did this girl, who could
have been anywhere in the world,

27:52.420 --> 27:56.080
[ Voice breaking ] been in
the just worst place possible?

27:56.080 --> 27:57.710
The whole world
is broken.

27:57.710 --> 27:58.920
Now I have a baby,

27:58.920 --> 28:01.830
and it just makes it
so much scarier.

28:01.830 --> 28:03.170
I can close.

28:03.170 --> 28:04.460
Thank you.

28:06.000 --> 28:08.500
[ Doors open ]

28:08.500 --> 28:12.830
♪♪

28:12.830 --> 28:13.880
[ Monitor beeps ]

28:13.880 --> 28:15.250
Get the drill ready.

28:15.250 --> 28:17.620
Stencil's
almost complete.

28:17.620 --> 28:18.960
You kidnapped
my surgery?

28:18.960 --> 28:21.330
Oh, it was never your surgery,
was it, Tom?

28:21.330 --> 28:23.380
Tap out, Shepherd.
I'm scrubbing in.

28:23.380 --> 28:25.120
Shepherd's actually
got it all under control.

28:25.120 --> 28:26.750
Uh, the family,
on the other hand,

28:26.750 --> 28:28.920
has had a change of heart about
you filming this whole thing.

28:28.920 --> 28:31.080
So if you get your camera crew
within -- I don't know --

28:31.080 --> 28:33.830
one foot of my O.R.,
security will be called.

28:33.830 --> 28:34.960
The foundation put me --

28:34.960 --> 28:36.250
I am the foundation.

28:36.250 --> 28:37.830
And I own more shares
than anyone on the board,

28:37.830 --> 28:40.080
so if you want to get technical,
I am your boss.

28:40.080 --> 28:41.580
Not to mention,
the people that come to me

28:41.580 --> 28:42.790
for cosmetic procedures

28:42.790 --> 28:44.880
make up a huge percentage
of hospital profits.

28:44.880 --> 28:47.380
So maybe you want to, um,
stay the hell out of my way.

28:47.380 --> 28:49.000
Wow.

28:49.000 --> 28:51.380
You just threw away millions
in fast, free publicity

28:51.380 --> 28:53.540
and took arrogance to a level
even I've never reached.

28:53.540 --> 28:55.290
This thing Grey started?

28:55.290 --> 28:56.670
You should know
better than anyone

28:56.670 --> 28:58.790
how fires like that
spread.

28:58.790 --> 29:01.960
And if it does, it'll burn down
a lot more than this hospital.

29:04.040 --> 29:07.290
Hey, Tom, great rage
in that reaction, really.

29:07.290 --> 29:09.040
But you were
a little backlit, though.

29:09.040 --> 29:11.420
I'd love it if you could
give it to me from the top,

29:11.420 --> 29:12.580
a little closer
to the door.

29:12.580 --> 29:13.830
[ Scoffs ]

29:13.830 --> 29:15.750
[ Chuckling ] Yeah.

29:15.750 --> 29:18.790
I was kinda hoping
my part would be done

29:18.790 --> 29:20.670
by the time
he found out.

29:20.670 --> 29:22.250
Yeah.
Sorry about that.

29:22.250 --> 29:24.040
Osteotome, please,
Schmitt.

29:25.330 --> 29:26.330
Schmitt, come on.

29:26.330 --> 29:27.670
Yeah. Sorry.

29:27.670 --> 29:28.670
Thank you.

29:31.750 --> 29:34.380
500 feet?
That's ridiculous.

29:34.380 --> 29:36.710
Bet it was worth it just to zap
the guy in the nads, though.

29:36.710 --> 29:39.580
It was an accident.
A happy accident.

29:39.580 --> 29:42.460
Bailey must be homicidal,
having Koracick as her boss.

29:42.460 --> 29:43.710
You a little bit happy
about that?

29:43.710 --> 29:45.790
Well, I mean,
I'm mad that she fired me,

29:45.790 --> 29:47.250
but Bailey's still Bailey.

29:47.250 --> 29:49.040
She shouldn't have to
take orders from him.

29:49.040 --> 29:50.710
That's exactly
why I left.

29:50.710 --> 29:52.580
Suction.

29:52.580 --> 29:54.540
So, you sick of it yet?
Staying home?

29:56.170 --> 29:59.750
I'm happy to do it
for Teddy.

29:59.750 --> 30:02.420
It's way harder
than I expected.

30:02.420 --> 30:04.710
Come work for me.
Take head of trauma.

30:04.710 --> 30:07.460
You know, structure
the department however
you want, ground up.

30:07.460 --> 30:09.830
I mean, Webber and I are
helping, but we can't do it all.

30:09.830 --> 30:12.040
I mean, look at this place.
It's really messed up.

30:12.040 --> 30:13.250
Way to sell it, Karev.

30:14.880 --> 30:16.620
Today was kinda fun.

30:16.620 --> 30:18.210
If there's one thing
I can promise you,

30:18.210 --> 30:19.750
it's that there'll be
more days like it.

30:19.750 --> 30:21.460
Kind of reminding me
of the Army.

30:21.460 --> 30:23.080
With worse food.
[ Chuckles ]

30:26.670 --> 30:29.580
Jackson: Alright, piece "S"
and "C" are in place.

30:29.580 --> 30:32.710
[ Natalie Taylor's
"I'll Stand By You" plays ]

30:32.710 --> 30:35.040
♪ Ohh ♪

30:35.040 --> 30:38.210
♪ Why you look so sad? ♪

30:38.210 --> 30:41.170
♪ Tears are in your eyes ♪

30:41.170 --> 30:45.170
♪ Come on and talk to me now ♪

30:45.170 --> 30:49.620
♪ Nothing you confess ♪

30:49.620 --> 30:52.880
♪ Could make me love you less ♪

30:52.880 --> 30:56.790
♪ Could make me love you less ♪

30:56.790 --> 30:59.920
♪ I'll stand by you ♪

30:59.920 --> 31:03.250
♪ I'll stand by you ♪

31:03.250 --> 31:06.420
♪ Won't let nobody hurt you ♪

31:06.420 --> 31:09.250
♪ Nobody hurt you ♪

31:09.250 --> 31:12.420
♪ I'll stand by you ♪

31:12.420 --> 31:15.790
♪ Take me in
into your darkest hour ♪

31:15.790 --> 31:19.000
♪ And I'll never desert you ♪

31:19.000 --> 31:21.960
♪ Never desert you ♪

31:21.960 --> 31:24.250
♪ I'll stand by you ♪

31:24.250 --> 31:30.080
♪♪

31:30.080 --> 31:35.920
♪♪

31:35.920 --> 31:38.460
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

31:38.460 --> 31:40.790
And...we're done.

31:41.920 --> 31:43.540
Everything fit.
It's perfect.

31:43.540 --> 31:46.380
Yeah.
Minimal blood loss.

31:46.380 --> 31:49.620
Alright, why don't you
get Clervie down to the PICU,

31:49.620 --> 31:50.960
and then
we'll update the family.

31:50.960 --> 31:53.710
I mean, it's perfect.
It's miraculous.

31:53.710 --> 31:55.250
And if you'd have let
Dr. Koracick film it,

31:55.250 --> 31:56.880
it might have really
helped this place.

31:56.880 --> 31:59.250
♪ I'll stand by you ♪

31:59.250 --> 32:01.210
I don't concern myself
with headlines, Schmitt.

32:01.210 --> 32:02.750
I suggest you don't,
either.

32:02.750 --> 32:04.250
You don't have to.

32:04.250 --> 32:05.290
You already
have a career.

32:05.290 --> 32:06.960
Your future is safe
no matter what.

32:06.960 --> 32:09.250
Not all of us
have that luxury.

32:09.250 --> 32:10.710
Alright,
you're so disappointed,

32:10.710 --> 32:13.210
why don't you get her bandaged
up and settled in the PICU,

32:13.210 --> 32:16.080
and I'll go
update the family myself.

32:16.080 --> 32:18.830
♪ Never desert you ♪

32:18.830 --> 32:22.000
♪ I'll stand by you ♪

32:22.000 --> 32:25.670
I remember telling security
to deactivate your keycard.

32:25.670 --> 32:27.330
I-I'm sure
this is a bad time.

32:27.330 --> 32:29.330
Uh, no.
A great time, in fact.

32:29.330 --> 32:31.290
I'm having
a red-letter day.

32:31.290 --> 32:32.960
There'll be cake
any minute.

32:32.960 --> 32:35.380
I would like to explain
how this happened.

32:35.380 --> 32:37.210
It was never meant
to be published.

32:37.210 --> 32:39.170
I only pitched them
a few ideas.

32:39.170 --> 32:41.380
From "Hospital Hell"?
That, I never even said.

32:41.380 --> 32:43.580
And I would never
say that.

32:43.580 --> 32:45.750
Anything
that I actually wrote

32:45.750 --> 32:48.330
wasn't even directed
at this hospital.

32:48.330 --> 32:50.120
Then have them change it.
Have them take it down.

32:50.120 --> 32:52.210
I tried.
They won't.

32:52.210 --> 32:55.040
I can write a retraction,
an explanation.

32:55.040 --> 32:57.080
[ Scoffs ] A retraction
won't help, Grey.

32:57.080 --> 32:59.380
Nobody reads
the retractions.

32:59.380 --> 33:01.920
Bailey, you know me.

33:01.920 --> 33:05.250
You know I love this place.
I grew up here.

33:05.250 --> 33:08.250
Any good I've ever done,
any awards I've ever received

33:08.250 --> 33:09.960
have been from things
I learned here,

33:09.960 --> 33:13.040
in this program,
from you and Richard Webber.

33:13.040 --> 33:14.960
[ Sighs ] I --

33:14.960 --> 33:18.120
I'm sorry if -- if any of this
has hurt you.

33:18.120 --> 33:20.000
I really am truly sorry.

33:21.790 --> 33:23.580
I know
what you learned, Grey.

33:23.580 --> 33:26.580
I spent years of my life
teaching it to you.

33:26.580 --> 33:29.040
Remember, I stayed late
almost every night

33:29.040 --> 33:31.330
explaining procedures
and technique

33:31.330 --> 33:33.250
when I could have been home
with my family, right?

33:33.250 --> 33:36.210
I made you study.
I made you practice.

33:36.210 --> 33:38.000
I was your friend,
your mentor,

33:38.000 --> 33:40.380
and every time you needed me,
I was there.

33:40.380 --> 33:42.710
So you can sit there
and apologize to me

33:42.710 --> 33:45.040
and say all the --
the moving words,

33:45.040 --> 33:46.710
but the damage
has been done.

33:46.710 --> 33:52.210
♪♪

33:52.210 --> 33:53.250
Bailey, I --

33:53.250 --> 33:55.080
You can close the door
on your way out.

33:55.080 --> 34:01.750
♪♪

34:01.750 --> 34:03.080
[ Door closes ]
[ Exhales sharply ]

34:09.330 --> 34:10.540
[ Teddy laughs ]

34:10.540 --> 34:12.000
A resident thought
that that was the aorta?

34:12.000 --> 34:13.420
What is wrong with people?
Owen: [ Laughing ] Yeah.

34:13.420 --> 34:14.710
If Karev hadn't been
giving me a tour,

34:14.710 --> 34:16.380
then the guy
might have died.

34:16.380 --> 34:17.540
W-- Y-You got a tour?

34:17.540 --> 34:18.540
Yeah.

34:18.540 --> 34:19.500
Evening, Altman.

34:19.500 --> 34:20.580
Hey.

34:20.580 --> 34:22.120
Leo!

34:22.120 --> 34:23.670
I'm not
turning around, Tom,

34:23.670 --> 34:25.420
so if you need to call the cops,
then go ahead.

34:25.420 --> 34:26.880
I'm dropping
the restraining order.

34:26.880 --> 34:28.120
We need every good doctor
we can get,

34:28.120 --> 34:30.040
so I'm taking
the high road.

34:30.040 --> 34:31.420
You can have
your job back.

34:32.790 --> 34:35.670
Yeah, well, thanks, but, um...
you didn't fire me.

34:35.670 --> 34:36.670
I quit.

34:36.670 --> 34:38.580
And I have already
taken a job

34:38.580 --> 34:40.670
at a very up-and-coming
area hospital.

34:40.670 --> 34:42.420
You did?
W-What hospital?

34:42.420 --> 34:45.040
One that will be excellent
when I'm done with it, so...

34:45.040 --> 34:46.460
It's Pac-North,
isn't it?

34:46.460 --> 34:47.580
It's not
a dirty word, Tom.

34:47.580 --> 34:49.330
Yeah,
but it's a dirty place.

34:49.330 --> 34:52.880
You call me when you realize
the error of your ways.

34:52.880 --> 34:54.710
Same to you.
[ Clicks tongue, chuckles ]

34:55.880 --> 34:57.830
Wow. Wow.
I hate that guy.

34:57.830 --> 34:59.000
[ Laughing ]
I know.

34:59.000 --> 35:00.000
[ Sighs ]

35:00.000 --> 35:01.170
Pac-North?
Mm-hmm.

35:01.170 --> 35:02.380
Really?

35:02.380 --> 35:04.540
Wait. Did you not read
Meredith's article?

35:04.540 --> 35:07.290
Your high horse
has no legs to stand on.

35:07.290 --> 35:09.120
[ Laughing ]
That is not the saying.

35:11.420 --> 35:14.420
Maggie: We did everything
we could do,

35:14.420 --> 35:17.500
but there was
just too much damage.

35:17.500 --> 35:18.710
I'm so sorry.

35:20.710 --> 35:23.580
Link: Do you have
any contact info

35:23.580 --> 35:26.500
for Alicia's folks
or any family we could call?

35:29.330 --> 35:34.290
We just met a month ago,
in biochem.

35:34.290 --> 35:36.670
I don't even know
her parents' names.

35:42.500 --> 35:44.120
Well...

35:44.120 --> 35:45.620
[ Clears throat ]

35:45.620 --> 35:47.830
It's okay.

35:47.830 --> 35:48.960
We'll find them.

35:53.500 --> 35:56.960
We were just sitting
in the grass

35:56.960 --> 36:00.120
under that tree.

36:00.120 --> 36:01.830
She liked that.

36:01.830 --> 36:05.880
She said it reminded her
of a Y.A. novel

36:05.880 --> 36:09.290
about teenagers
who had cancer

36:09.290 --> 36:12.380
enjoying life and grass
and the air

36:12.380 --> 36:13.710
while they still could,

36:13.710 --> 36:15.880
except we didn't have to
have cancer.

36:17.580 --> 36:18.580
[ Sighs ]

36:18.580 --> 36:21.170
We would just lie
in the grass

36:21.170 --> 36:23.040
and look at each other.

36:23.040 --> 36:25.460
♪♪

36:25.460 --> 36:29.330
It felt cheesy at first,
but then...

36:31.920 --> 36:34.620
[Voice breaking] ...it was
all I wanted to do forever.

36:34.620 --> 36:36.790
[ Sobbing ]

36:39.120 --> 36:42.540
I should have
protected her.

36:42.540 --> 36:46.460
But how do you protect someone
from something like this?

36:46.460 --> 36:48.210
[ Sobbing continues ]

36:48.210 --> 36:50.380
♪♪

36:50.380 --> 36:52.580
Hey. Hey. Hey.

36:52.580 --> 36:54.830
[ Sobbing continues ]

36:54.830 --> 36:58.960
♪♪

37:00.880 --> 37:02.420
[ Telephone ringing ]

37:07.170 --> 37:08.670
Hey!
Hey.

37:08.670 --> 37:11.080
You, uh, lost?
You looking for the E.R.?

37:11.080 --> 37:12.670
No, I just
dropped off a guy

37:12.670 --> 37:14.380
whose bowling ball pulled him
all the way down the alley.

37:14.380 --> 37:16.040
So, this one of yours?

37:16.040 --> 37:17.380
Okay.
[ Chuckles ]

37:17.380 --> 37:18.670
Uh, yeah.

37:18.670 --> 37:20.790
Yeah, I just rebuilt
this little girl's skull

37:20.790 --> 37:22.830
from scratch,
actually.

37:22.830 --> 37:24.170
Took all day.

37:26.250 --> 37:27.830
That's it?

37:27.830 --> 37:29.620
Usually you're all,

37:29.620 --> 37:31.000
"I was the only surgeon in
the whole world who could do it

37:31.000 --> 37:33.000
'cause I'm so skilled."

37:33.000 --> 37:35.580
I mean, I wouldn't say
the whole world, first of all.
Uh-huh.

37:35.580 --> 37:38.500
The state of Washington
is an argument.

37:38.500 --> 37:41.170
I'd be lying
if I said I wasn't impressed.

37:41.170 --> 37:42.380
♪♪

37:42.380 --> 37:44.170
I'm suddenly starving.
You got 10 minutes?

37:44.170 --> 37:45.620
Can I interest you

37:45.620 --> 37:47.920
in some particularly disgusting
hospital food?

37:47.920 --> 37:49.670
Oh, my God,
that's my favorite.

37:49.670 --> 37:52.670
Meredith:
After multiple transfusions,
emergent dialysis,

37:52.670 --> 37:55.540
and the fastest central line
I've done to this day,

37:55.540 --> 37:57.290
my patient pulled through.

37:57.290 --> 37:58.710
You're sure
you want to do this?

37:58.710 --> 37:59.880
But it taught
an important lesson.

37:59.880 --> 38:01.330
Let me have it.

38:01.330 --> 38:04.830
Okay. But I'm warning you,
it is habit-forming.

38:04.830 --> 38:06.670
There is no such thing
as a routine surgery.

38:06.670 --> 38:08.750
[ Laughs ]

38:08.750 --> 38:10.670
[ Groans ]

38:10.670 --> 38:12.250
[ Exhales deeply ]

38:12.250 --> 38:15.540
[ Both laughing ]

38:15.540 --> 38:18.210
♪ 'Cause I've waited
a long, long time ♪

38:18.210 --> 38:21.790
♪ To remember
all that you've done for me ♪

38:21.790 --> 38:23.170
Amelia?

38:23.170 --> 38:26.120
♪ And I'm drawing
a long, long line ♪

38:26.120 --> 38:27.500
I think
I'm in love with you.

38:27.500 --> 38:30.420
♪♪

38:30.420 --> 38:31.880
And I know you said
not to say it back,

38:31.880 --> 38:34.500
but it's not something
I feel very often.

38:34.500 --> 38:39.380
Love is...
not really my thing.

38:39.380 --> 38:41.500
Dating, yes.

38:41.500 --> 38:42.750
Fun, yes.

38:42.750 --> 38:44.920
Sex, yes.

38:44.920 --> 38:49.120
Love...leads to divorce.

38:50.380 --> 38:51.880
Leads to pain.

38:51.880 --> 38:53.540
I think that's been
my world view.

38:53.540 --> 38:56.750
♪♪

38:56.750 --> 38:58.000
But I'm feeling it.

38:59.920 --> 39:01.460
I'm pretty sure.

39:01.460 --> 39:03.040
And...

39:05.000 --> 39:06.960
...it's a feeling I like.

39:06.960 --> 39:08.880
It's a feeling
I want to name.

39:08.880 --> 39:12.170
♪♪

39:12.170 --> 39:15.210
Because sometimes
people fall out of the sky,

39:15.210 --> 39:19.750
so there's kinda no point
in trying to avoid pain.

39:19.750 --> 39:23.250
♪ To remember
all that you've done for me ♪

39:23.250 --> 39:25.420
♪♪

39:25.420 --> 39:26.620
Okay.

39:26.620 --> 39:30.380
♪ In between
the dark and the light ♪

39:30.380 --> 39:33.790
Every time I step
into an O.R...

39:33.790 --> 39:35.460
I'm ready for the worst.

39:37.000 --> 39:38.210
Hey.
Hey.

39:38.210 --> 39:39.710
What -- What are you
doing here?

39:39.710 --> 39:41.120
I tried
to talk to Bailey.

39:42.620 --> 39:44.540
She thinks
I attacked her publicly.

39:44.540 --> 39:45.710
It's -- I don't know.

39:45.710 --> 39:47.420
I don't -- I don't know
how to fix this.

39:47.420 --> 39:49.460
I mean, what --
what were you expecting?

39:49.460 --> 39:51.000
We're friends.

39:51.000 --> 39:54.170
I thought our history would earn
me some benefit of the doubt.

39:54.170 --> 39:55.580
And I walked off
work crew,

39:55.580 --> 39:57.620
so I got a summons
to go back to court.

39:57.620 --> 39:58.830
Wait a minute.
You walked out?

39:58.830 --> 39:59.920
Well, I had no choice.

39:59.920 --> 40:01.580
Mer, yeah,
you did have a choice.

40:01.580 --> 40:03.000
And -- And you chose the thing
that could put you in jail.

40:03.000 --> 40:04.250
Why would you do that?

40:04.250 --> 40:06.670
That headline
hurt a lot of people.

40:06.670 --> 40:07.960
You once told me
I needed to develop

40:07.960 --> 40:09.250
an instinct
for self-preservation.

40:09.250 --> 40:11.040
Remember that?
That was
entirely different.

40:11.040 --> 40:12.710
You were claiming a crime
you didn't commit.

40:12.710 --> 40:14.670
Yeah, a-a crime
that you committed.

40:14.670 --> 40:16.920
A crime that's now threatening
your medical license.

40:16.920 --> 40:18.380
And this is just adding
to that threat.

40:18.380 --> 40:20.580
You think the medical board
just doesn't read the news?

40:20.580 --> 40:22.620
There isn't anything that I said
that wasn't the truth.

40:24.420 --> 40:26.750
It isn't my fault that they
packaged it up like a bomb.

40:26.750 --> 40:28.880
Okay, but don't you think
that there was a world

40:28.880 --> 40:31.670
where you just finish
the community-service hours
and came back to work?

40:31.670 --> 40:35.250
I should just shut up and sit
on my mountain of privilege?

40:35.250 --> 40:37.380
And leave everyone else
to fight their own battles?

40:37.380 --> 40:40.170
Or you work within
the broken system to change it

40:40.170 --> 40:41.960
instead of bringing
the whole thing down with you.

40:41.960 --> 40:43.880
It's self-destructive, Mer.

40:43.880 --> 40:45.580
You really don't need enemies
right now.

40:45.580 --> 40:48.330
No. I don't.

40:48.330 --> 40:50.170
And I don't need this,
either.

40:50.170 --> 40:51.580
And if you think
there's a world

40:51.580 --> 40:53.920
in which I just sit back
while something's broken

40:53.920 --> 40:57.210
and hurting people
and killing people...

40:57.210 --> 40:58.210
you don't really know me.

40:59.670 --> 41:01.960
At all.

41:01.960 --> 41:04.710
It's not a guarantee
against bad outcomes,

41:04.710 --> 41:07.210
but it does mean,
when the curveballs come,

41:07.210 --> 41:08.620
when the sky starts to fall...

41:08.620 --> 41:10.580
[ Knock on door ]
♪ You'll turn your head ♪

41:10.580 --> 41:11.960
♪ Leave me unwanted ♪

41:11.960 --> 41:14.000
Well?

41:14.000 --> 41:17.830
Your blood work indicates
that you are perimenopausal...

41:17.830 --> 41:19.080
[ Groans ]

41:21.080 --> 41:23.210
Uh, there was an ellipsis
in your voice.

41:24.170 --> 41:26.420
You're also pregnant,
Bailey.

41:27.580 --> 41:29.170
I'm sorry?

41:29.170 --> 41:30.750
Your bloodwork
shows that --

41:30.750 --> 41:31.880
No.

41:31.880 --> 41:34.380
D-- I-I --
It's hormones.

41:34.380 --> 41:36.080
It's, uh, hot flashes,
mood swings.

41:36.080 --> 41:37.420
I'm -- It's menopause.

41:37.420 --> 41:40.170
Yeah, your beta-HCG
isn't lying.

41:40.170 --> 41:42.460
You can be perimenopausal
and still shed eggs.

41:42.460 --> 41:43.960
I don't understand.

41:43.960 --> 41:46.330
You are both perimenopausal
and pregna--

41:46.330 --> 41:50.210
I heard you.
I just don't understand.

41:50.210 --> 41:51.960
...hopefully you're less likely

41:51.960 --> 41:54.000
to get completely
knocked off your feet.

41:55.500 --> 41:57.790
Please tell me you don't plan
to keep this a secret.

41:57.790 --> 41:59.420
[ Exhales sharply ]

41:59.420 --> 42:02.040
♪ Please give me space
where I can belong ♪

42:02.040 --> 42:06.330
♪♪

42:14.460 --> 42:23.580
♪♪

42:23.580 --> 42:32.750
♪♪

42:32.750 --> 42:41.960
♪♪

42:44.620 --> 42:46.960
♪♪
